CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 7, 1962, pg. 5, reads: "Scranton in Hill District - Congressman William W. Scranton, gubernatorial candidate on the Republican ticket, made a whirlwind tour of the city's Hill District, Monday morning, to see at first hand and to shake hands with voters. Accompanied by his wife, Mrs. Mary Scranton, he stopped at... (3) a delegation from Johnstown (Cambria County), including a group of enthusiastic Young Republicans. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group surrounding Pennsylvania gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton and Mary Scranton, in front of Pittsburgh Courier newspaper building
